Date: 0/0/1840
Source: Plain Truths
Author: JOHNSTON
Vol / Page: 61
Edition:
Quote: The whalers all sail upon the lay, ... or, every person on board receives, according to a graduated scale, a portion of oil which is to be given up as per agreement, to the employers at a certain price, not above half the amount they would obtain for it, were they to sell it themselves at Sydney.
